com.mobius.vdrapi.command
Class FindCommand

java.lang.Object
  |

All Implemented Interfaces:
ICanPromptForKeyValue, ICommand, INeedFullLoginCredentials, INeedLoginCredentials, com.mobius.vdrapi.callbacks.INeedLoginCredentialsEx, INeedObjectWithPage, INeedObjectWithProfileLocation, com.mobius.vdrapi.callbacks.INeedObjectWithSearchHitList, INeedObjectWithSession, INeedObjectWithTraceThreshold, INeedPromptForKeyValue
public class FindCommand
extends com.mobius.vdrapi.command.PromptingCommandBase
implements INeedObjectWithPage, INeedObjectWithSession, INeedLoginCredentials, com.mobius.vdrapi.callbacks.INeedLoginCredentialsEx, INeedFullLoginCredentials, INeedObjectWithProfileLocation, INeedObjectWithTraceThreshold, com.mobius.vdrapi.callbacks.INeedObjectWithSearchHitList

This command object is used to retrieve a page that contains the first occurance of the specified search string. It has the following parameters:

  • DOCUMENTSERVER "xxxxxx" - this required parameter specifies the document server to connect to. If the document server needs to prompt for a user ID or password, the Find command makes a callback to IHasLoginCredentials.

    A document server's default trace threshold level (message logging) is set to ViewDirectSeverityLevel.SL_DISASTER, the minimum tracing level. To change the document server's trace threshold level, implement the IHasTraceThreshold interface, and assign the object to this command via setObjectWithTraceThreshold(IHasTraceThreshold traceThreshold).

  • REPORTID "xxxxxx" - this required parameter specifies the report ID where the page is located.

  • VERSIONID "xxxxx" - this optional parameter specifies the report version ID where the page is located, and should be of the form "YYYYMMDDHHMMSS" When a version ID isn't specified, the most recent version in the report archive is used.

  • SECTIONID "xxxxx" - this parameter specifies the report section in which to begin searching for the text string. It is only required when the search origin is designated Relative. If the search origin is designated Global, this parameter is ignored.

  • PAGE "xx" - this parameter specifies the page of the specified section on which to begin searching for the text string. It is only required when the search origin is designated Relative. When the Page value is positive, the search starts from the section and page specified (e.g. if Page = 2, the search starts at the second page of the specified section). If the value is negative, the search begins that number of pages before the beginning of the specified section. (for example, if Page = -2, the search starts two pages before the begining of the specified section.) Zero is not a valid page number; passing in a value of zero results in an error. If the search origin is Global, this parameter is ignored.

  • SUBPAGE "xx" - this parameter specifies the subpage of the specified report page on which to begin searching for the text string. It is only required when the search origin is designated Relative and the report is an associated type. Zero is not a valid subpage number; passing in a value of zero results in an error. If the search origin is Global, this parameter is ignored.

  • SEARCHSTRING - this required parameter is the text that is searched for.

  • SEARCHPAGELIMIT "xx" - this parameter specifies the number of pages to search, if the search scope parameter value is Page. If the search scope is not Page, this parameter is ignored. The search page limit must be a positive number greater than zero.

  • SEARCHSCOPE "xxxxxxx" - this optional parameter specifies a scope for the search. It can be set to "Section", which limits the search to the current section only. It can be set to "Page", which limits the search to to the number of pages specified by the Search Page Limit parameter. It can also be set to "Eof", which indicates the search should extend through to the end of the archive. If this parameter is not specified, the default value of "Eof" is assumed.

  • SEARCHORIGIN "xxxxxxxx" - this optional parameter specifies the start point of the search. "Global" indicates the search starts at the begining of the archive for a forward search, and at the end of the archive for a backward search. "Relative" indicates the search starts from the specified section and page. If this parameter is not specified, the default value of "Global" is assumed.

  • CASESENSITIVE - this optional parameter specifies whether or not the search is case sensitive. If the value is TRUE, the case of the search string is taken into account. If the value is FALSE, the case of the search string is ignored. If this parameter is not specified, the the default value of FALSE is assumed.

  • FORWARDSEARCH - this optional parameter specified whether or not the search is a forward-directional search or a backward-directional search. If the value is TRUE, the search is a forward search. If the value is FALSE, the search is a backward search. If this parameter is not specified, the default value of TRUE is assumed.

Note:
  • The FindCommand implements the INeedLoginCredentials and INeedFullLoginCredentials interfaces. However, the caller should implement either IHasLoginCredentials or IHasFullLoginCredentials but not both. If both interfaces are implemented, the command throws a MultipleCallbacksSetException.

  • If the caller implements the IHoldSession interface, then neither IHasLoginCredentials nor IHasFullLoginCredentials is required.

execute

public void execute()
             throws CommandNotLoadedException,
                    CallbackException,
                    ViewDirectException
Executes the command that creates a session for the specified document server (if an existing session has not already been provided), and opens an archive for the specified report and version. It then retrieves page data using the specified input parameters. After retrieving the page data from the server, the command creates an IPage object and returns it to the caller in the ObjectWithPage callback object.

setObjectWithSession

public void setObjectWithSession(IHoldSession objectWithSession)
Sets the callback object.

Under normal circumstances, the Find command creates its own session internally, which it then uses to perform its function. This optional callback enables the caller to provide an existing session for the command to use, rather having to create its own session. When provided, the session must be connected to the document server specified in the load parameters.

Specified by:
setObjectWithSession in interface INeedObjectWithSession
Parameters:
objectWithSession - object called when this class requires a session.
